  <title>Remove a Branch</title>

  <note style="warning">
    <p>Any information related to the deleted branch will be deleted and cannot be restored.</p>
    <p>This includes all employees of the said branch and their time records.</p>
  </note>

  <p>To remove a branch:</p>
  <steps>
    <item><p>Log in to the Control Panel.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click the <gui style="tab">Branches</gui> tab.</p></item>
    <item><p>Select the branches you want to remove from the list.</p></item>
    <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui style="menu">Edit</gui><gui style="menuitem">Remove</gui></guiseq>, or press <key>Delete</key>, or click <gui style="button">Remove</gui> in the toolbar.</p></item>
  </steps>

  <note style="tip">
    <p>You may select multiple branches by dragging, or clicking each one while pressing <key>Ctrl</key>.</p>
    <p>You may also right-click on the list to show the context menu instead, where you could select <gui style="menuitem">Remove</gui> to remove the currently selected branches.</p>
  </note>

